@NODE Introduction                   Gallery.guide/Introduction

     @{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 This program is intended for creating nice looking HTML pages with small 
 thumbnails of pictures. It creates a gallery where you can click through 
 (in order to see the pictures). 
 
 This piece of software is written in a forthcomming C++ class library for 
 the Amiga, which is easy to use and intuitive. Just have a look into the
 program sources to see how this class library is being used. If you are 
 interested in this class library, feel free to contact me. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements                   Gallery.guide/Requirements

     @{u}@{b}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

 To use this program, you will need the following things:
 
 - AmigaOS 3.0
 - 68020 at least
 - fillbar.image  (included in this package) by Antonio Santos
 - render.library (included in this package) by Timm S. Müller
 - guigfx.library (included in this package) by Timm S. Müller
 - JPEG Codec     (included in this package) by Christoph Feck

@ENDNODE

@NODE Codec                          Gallery.guide/Tower JPEG codec class

